3|Sift the dry ingredients together. 
3|The dry ingredients are: flour, sugar, salt, baking soda, and cocoa. 
3|Simply place everything in a sifter and shake it back and forth over a bowl to eliminate the clumps.
3|Stir in the liquid ingredients and stir well. 
3|These are the vinegar, oil, vanilla, water and egg. 
3|Some people like to add these ingredients individually, but others stir them together in a second bowl and before adding them to the dry ingredients.
4|Pour the mixture into an 8-inch greased and floured round pan. 
2|The grease and flour will keep the mix from sticking to the pan.
4|Bake at 350 °F (177 °C). (175 C.) for 30 minutes.
5|Let the cake cool for 5 minutes.
6|Frost as desired.
